				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><blockquote>Yesterday on <a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/"target=blank>EQ Live</a> the EverQuest development team released some information regarding class balancing issues, and changes you can expect to see in the upcoming patch (<a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/support/scheduled_downtime.jsp"target=blank>Wednesday, October 16th</a>). <br><br>

Changes are being made to:<br>
<blockquote><li>Wizard Alternate Advancement - specifically Manaburn
<li>The use of Rods of Mystical Transvergence
<li>Cleric's Complete Healing hitpoints cap
<li>Monk defense and Armor Class</blockquote>

The scale of changes being made is large, and talk has already been growing in our <a href="http://www.everlore.com/MB_SHOW.asp?FID=76&FN=MainHall&SID=7&SN=Everlore&TID=1726368&TN=Best+Patch%2E+Ever%2E&CAT=General&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&PL=3"target=blank>Main Hall</a>. Opinions seem to be mixed; What some are calling crucial class-balancing changes, others are calling an unnecessary nerf. Click <a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/articles.jsp?id=52118"target=blank>here</a> to read the full article submitted by the EQ Development Team, and then come back to let us know what <b>you</b> think.</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
